                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (1) When the temperatures finally started rising, we made a trip to a local playground and had so much fun! I have learned that I really do take our beautiful weather for granted. While we do have three or four months of pure hot misery (in my opinion), the rest of the year is pretty much nice and beautiful."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) Daniel and I did a date night downtown one evening. It was so foggy out that you couldn't see the top of this building!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) We ordered Franklin's BBQ for Daniel's birthday celebration. It was delayed twice for the weather, but when we finally had it, we all loved it, including Caden! He's going to be a baby BBQ snob since his first experience was Franklin's!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4) We made the trip to Waco the last weekend of the month. I was able to say goodbye to my sweet, sweet Mimi, and we got to give Papa lots of hugs. Please pray for my Papa during this time as he continues to mourn the loss of his wife of 65 years and settles into this new phase of life without her by his side."
          }
        ]
